# Printing and Export Rules

- DataMatrix must be encoded from the normalized payload with real GS `0x1D`.
- Escaped `[GS]` is display-only and must not be used for DataMatrix encoding or print payloads.
- PDF label output must use the exact selected template size.
- Do not silently fall back to A4 for label printing.
- Do not send Chestny ZNAK payloads, AI91/AI92 crypto tails, or exports outside the local machine.
- Keep print/export changes covered by focused tests when behavior changes.
- Preserve existing template dimensions, DataMatrix placement, and copy count semantics unless explicitly requested.
